					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I have no idea how the SNES PPU works internally at all, but if it's anything like the Mega Drive, it doesn't cache the tilemaps at all but reads them on-the-fly as it rasters. No idea if the mosaic data is cached, though (which could be a possibility, especially since it can work with non-power-of-two values). It's also possible it may work, but only on a 16 pixel granularity (considering that mosaic seems to work on that step amount).<br /><br />Is there any research on how the SNES PPU renders each scanline? Maybe Byuu has more info?</div>

